Ian Holloway insisted he will have to discipline Matthew Briggs after the defender was sent off against Wycombe Wanderers last night.

Briggs took his shirt off after scoring what turned out to be the winner in the first half. Referee Andy D'Urso booked the defender for his celebration, and then showed him a second yellow for a reckless challenge after the break.

Holloway said: 'I’m going to have to discipline Briggsy. You’ve just got to keep your shirt on, haven’t you? It was totally unprofessional.'

