The 23-year-old defender replied: 'It was silly and won’t happen again.'

Holloway's side have enjoyed a strong start to the season. They beat Leeds 2-0 in their Championship opener and last night they saw off Wycombe 1-0 in the Capital One Cup.

Next up for The Lions is a trip across London as they face Championship new boys Fulham at Craven Cottage. Millwall will host Holloway's old side Blackpool later his month.

